      "content": "wait, r u saying the argument about disincentives is just \"politically motivated\"? that seems a bit one-sided. a lot of economists and policymakers argue that if the gap between benefits and a low-wage job is too small, it's just basic math why someone wouldn't want to jump back into work. isn't that a legitimate economic concern rather than just a political talking point?",
