      "content": "The concern about benefit cliffs and marginal tax rates is a legitimate economic principle, and it is a core focus of fiscal policy debates. However, framing it as a purely \"political talking point\" is an oversimplification; it is a genuine structural issue that policymakers must address. The real debate is whether the incentive structure should prioritize maximizing labor participation or ensuring a dignified standard of living for all citizens.",
      "source": "target",
